{"cells":[{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"# Lab: Create and Query Persistable Types","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Overview","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"C3 Types are the foundations of all C3 AI applications. In this lab, you create Types for a demand-tracking application for a merchandise store chain. \n\n<div class=\"alert alert-success\">\n    Each learning objective corresponds with a <b>#TODO</b> in the notebook activities.\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Estimated time","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"This lab will take approximately **1 hour** to complete.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Learning objectives","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"After completing this lab, you will be able to:\n- Create Types in an application package.\n- Write Type records to the server.\n- Query data loaded into Persistable Types.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Lab support","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"For guidance on the activities, please refer to the <a href=\"../src/doc/create-and-query-persistable-types-solution.c3doc.md\">solutions</a>. You can also refer to the [troubleshooting tips and tricks](../labs/troubleshooting.md) if you run into issues.\n\nFor additional support, check out the <a href=\"https://learn.c3.ai/page/help-center\" target=\"_blank\">Help Center</a> for office hours information.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Setup","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"When you complete this C3 notebook, you want to run the commands against the right application. Before you continue with the lab, open the dropdown menu by selecting **Select Application** in the toolbar. This displays a list of applications in your environment. Choose the application with `root package: academyFundamentals`. \n\n\nIn the following image, the application with the root package `academyfundamentals` is selected:\n\n<img src=\"../src/doc/img/lab2/app-dropdown.png\" alt=\"The dropdown menu with the academyfundamentals application selected.\" width=\"700px\" style=\"padding: inherit; margin:auto; display:block;\"/> ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Introduction","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"The chain store company, Bigger Box Stores, recently started working using C3 AI to centralize their forecasting and analytics systems across the United States. Currently, the software used by each region across the country is different and the central office would like to unify these systems.\n\nIn this lab, you use the C3 AI Type System to build the beginnings of an application data model to prototype this new forecasting application. \n\nIn the activities, you add new fields to the `City` and `Store` Types, which already exist in your application, and build three new Types: `Sale`, `LineItem`, and `Product`. Refer to the following image to see the what you build in Section 1 of the lab. `PK` indicates that the field is a primary key. ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<img src=\"../src/doc/img/lab1/intro.png\" alt=\"Entity relationship diagram of the types created in this lab.\" width=\"800px\" style=\"padding: inherit; margin:auto; display:block;\">","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Section 1: Create Persistable Types","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"The new application revolves around the `Store` Type, so that store managers know what to stock. The application package provided has two skeleton Types created already, `City.c3typ` and `Store.c3typ`. \n\nLocate the type files in `academyFundamentals/src/base/`. These two Types each have one field defined. In this section, you complete the Type definitions and create a new Type.\n\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n<h4>Activity 1.1</h4>\n\nComplete the <b>Store.c3typ</b> implementation.\n</div>\n\nFinish the Type definition with the following requirements:\n- Add the `entity` keyword to make `Store` a Persistable Type.\n- Add the fields to the Type:\n    - latitude - a float value, that represents the latitude of the store's location.\n    - longitude - a float value, that represents the longitude of the store's location.\n    - city - a string value, that indicates the city the store is located in.\n\nMake sure to include docstrings for your fields.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n<h4>Activity 1.2</h4>\n\nAdd fields to <b>City.c3typ</b>.\n</div>\n\nFinish the `City` Type definition by adding the following fields:\n- population - an integer value, that indicates the population of the city.\n- salesTaxRate - a float value, that indicates the sales tax rate applied to transactions in the city.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n<h4>Activity 1.3</h4>\n\nCreate the <code>Sale</code> Type definition in your application package. \n</div>\n\nCreate the **Sale.c3typ** file. The Type definition should meet the following requirements:\n\nThe new Type should satisfy the following requirements:\n- Is a Persistable Type.\n- Includes the following fields:\n    - date - a datetime value that indicates when the transaction was made.\n    - paymentMethod - a string that denotes the type of payment method used for the transaction.\n    - store - a string that indicates which store the transaction was made at.\n    - totalPrice - a double that indicates the total price of the transaction.\n\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">\n<b>Note:</b> Remember that Type definitions must be created in the <code>src</code> folder of your application package. Otherwise, you are free to organize them however you want within the <code>src</code> folder.\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n<h4>Activity 1.4</h4>\n\nCreate the <code>LineItem</code> Type definition in your application package.\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Create **LineItem.c3typ**. The Type definition should meet the following requirements:\n\n- Is a Persistable Type.\n- Includes the fields:\n    - sale - a string value, that indicates which sale the line item is part of.\n    - quantity - a float value, that indicates the quantity of the product being purchased. \n    - price - a float value, the price of the product at the time of purchase.\n    - product - a string value, that indicates the product purchased in this line item record. ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n<h4>Activity 1.5</h4>\n\nCreate the <code>Product</code> Type definition in your application package.\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Create **Product.c3typ**. The Type definition should meet the following requirements:\n\n- Is a Persistable Type.\n- Include the fields:\n    - name - a string value, representing the name of the product.\n    - description - a string value, containing the description of the product.\n    - category - a string value, indicating the category of the product.\n    - unitPrice - a float value, the price for a single unit of the product.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Section 2: Create and update Type records","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Now that we have Types defined, let's practice creating Type records. The following cell contains an example of creating a Type record for the `City` Type. ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// The `make()` method creates an instance of a Type in memory.\n// To persist the Type to the database, you must run `create()`, `upsert()`, or `merge()`.\nCity.make({\n    id: \"RWC\", // Specify the ID here for the record. If empty, a random ID is generated.\n    name: \"Redwood City\",\n    population: 84292,\n    salesTaxRate: 9.8\n}).create()","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"c3/notebook","value":["{","\t\"kind\": \"JSON\",","\t\"output\": {","\t\t\"data\": {","\t\t\t\"id\": \"RWC\",","\t\t\t\"name\": \"Redwood City\",","\t\t\t\"meta\": {","\t\t\t\t\"created\": \"2026-05-21T18:11:15Z\",","\t\t\t\t\"updated\": \"2026-05-21T18:11:15Z\",","\t\t\t\t\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-21T18:11:15Z\"","\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\"version\": 1","\t\t},","\t\t\"isGriddable\": false,","\t\t\"isChartable\": false,","\t\t\"chartMeta\": null","\t},","\t\"settings\": {","\t\t\"privateFields\": false,","\t\t\"maxHeight\": 540,","\t\t\"gridRows\": 100,","\t\t\"theme\": \"Default Dark Modern\"","\t}","}"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779387075053,"endTime":1779387077129},"executionOrder":1,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Try populating the Type with another record. Complete the following activity to add another `City` record to your application.\n\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n<h4>Activity 2.1</h4>\n\nCreate a <code>City</code> record with the following fields:\n<ul>\n    <li>id: NYC</li>\n    <li>name: New York City</li>\n    <li>population: 8478072</li>\n    <li>salesTaxRate: 8.875</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// TODO: Create the City record for New York City\n\n// The `make()` method creates an instance of a Type in memory.\n// To persist the Type to the database, you must run `create()`, `upsert()`, or `merge()`.\nCity.make({\n    id: \"NYC\", // Specify the ID here for the record. If empty, a random ID is generated.\n    name: \"New York City\",\n    population: 8478072,\n    salesTaxRate: 8.875\n}).create()","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"c3/notebook","value":["{","\t\"kind\": \"JSON\",","\t\"output\": {","\t\t\"data\": {","\t\t\t\"id\": \"NYC\",","\t\t\t\"name\": \"New York City\",","\t\t\t\"meta\": {","\t\t\t\t\"created\": \"2026-05-21T18:12:01Z\",","\t\t\t\t\"updated\": \"2026-05-21T18:12:01Z\",","\t\t\t\t\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-21T18:12:01Z\"","\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\"version\": 1","\t\t},","\t\t\"isGriddable\": false,","\t\t\"isChartable\": false,","\t\t\"chartMeta\": null","\t},","\t\"settings\": {","\t\t\"privateFields\": false,","\t\t\"maxHeight\": 540,","\t\t\"gridRows\": 100,","\t\t\"theme\": \"Default Dark Modern\"","\t}","}"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779387121512,"endTime":1779387121580},"executionOrder":2,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"The sales tax rate in Redwood City was entered in error. It should be 9.875%, not 9.8. Your colleague provided a command for you to run. \n\nRun the following cell to update the `salesTaxRate` to 9.875 for the \"RWC\" record.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"City.make({\n    id:\"RWC\", \n    salesTaxRate: 9.875\n}).upsert().get() // get() retrieves the object and all of its fields","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"c3/notebook","value":["{","\t\"kind\": \"JSON\",","\t\"output\": {","\t\t\"data\": {","\t\t\t\"id\": \"RWC\",","\t\t\t\"meta\": {","\t\t\t\t\"appCode\": 1865745090558541600,","\t\t\t\t\"env\": \"srinat\",","\t\t\t\t\"app\": \"academyfundamentals\",","\t\t\t\t\"created\": \"2026-05-21T18:11:15Z\",","\t\t\t\t\"createdBy\": \"sriram.natarajan@c3.ai\",","\t\t\t\t\"updated\": \"2026-05-21T18:12:13Z\",","\t\t\t\t\"updatedBy\": \"sriram.natarajan@c3.ai\",","\t\t\t\t\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-21T18:12:13Z\",","\t\t\t\t\"fetchInclude\": \"[]\",","\t\t\t\t\"fetchType\": \"City\"","\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\"version\": 2,","\t\t\t\"salesTaxRate\": 9.875","\t\t},","\t\t\"isGriddable\": false,","\t\t\"isChartable\": false,","\t\t\"chartMeta\": null","\t},","\t\"settings\": {","\t\t\"privateFields\": false,","\t\t\"maxHeight\": 540,","\t\t\"gridRows\": 100,","\t\t\"theme\": \"Default Dark Modern\"","\t}","}"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779387133562,"endTime":1779387133667},"executionOrder":3,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Inspect the output of the previous cell. You may have noticed that the only fields present are `id` and `salesTaxRate`. Since the last call used upsert, the other fields defined on the record have been replaced with null!\n\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n<h4>Activity 2.2</h4>\n\nAdd the <code>name</code> and <code>population</code> fields back to the record with the ID \"RWC.\" Refer to the code cell at the beginning of Section 2 for the field values.\n\n<b>Note:</b> Use the <code>make()</code> and <code>merge()</code> methods to avoid upserting any other fields to null.\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// TODO: Repopulate the name and population fields for RWC.\n\nCity.make({\n    id: \"RWC\", // Specify the ID here for the record. If empty, a random ID is generated.\n    name: \"Redwood City\",\n    population: 84292}).merge().get()","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"c3/notebook","value":["{","\t\"kind\": \"JSON\",","\t\"output\": {","\t\t\"data\": {","\t\t\t\"id\": \"RWC\",","\t\t\t\"name\": \"Redwood City\",","\t\t\t\"meta\": {","\t\t\t\t\"appCode\": 1865745090558541600,","\t\t\t\t\"env\": \"srinat\",","\t\t\t\t\"app\": \"academyfundamentals\",","\t\t\t\t\"created\": \"2026-05-21T18:11:15Z\",","\t\t\t\t\"createdBy\": \"sriram.natarajan@c3.ai\",","\t\t\t\t\"updated\": \"2026-05-21T18:14:09Z\",","\t\t\t\t\"updatedBy\": \"sriram.natarajan@c3.ai\",","\t\t\t\t\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-21T18:14:09Z\",","\t\t\t\t\"fetchInclude\": \"[]\",","\t\t\t\t\"fetchType\": \"City\"","\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\"version\": 3,","\t\t\t\"population\": 84292,","\t\t\t\"salesTaxRate\": 9.875","\t\t},","\t\t\"isGriddable\": false,","\t\t\"isChartable\": false,","\t\t\"chartMeta\": null","\t},","\t\"settings\": {","\t\t\"privateFields\": false,","\t\t\"maxHeight\": 540,","\t\t\"gridRows\": 100,","\t\t\"theme\": \"Default Dark Modern\"","\t}","}"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779387271225,"endTime":1779387271298},"executionOrder":5,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"You received some additional test data to test your application with. In the following activity, you are provided with lists of `Store` and `Product` records, respectively defined in the `stores` and `products` variables.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n<h4>Activity 2.3</h4>\n\nPersist the records in <code>stores</code> to the <code>Store</code> Type and the records in <code>products</code> to the <code>Product</code> Type. You can complete this iteratively or with batch methods.\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"stores = [{id: 'store_001', address: '123 Market St', city: 'city_001', latitude: 37.7749, longitude: -122.4194}, {id: 'store_002', address: '456 Mission St', city: 'city_001', latitude: 37.7849, longitude: -122.4094}, {id: 'store_003', address: '789 Castro St', city: 'city_001', latitude: 37.7609, longitude: -122.435}, {id: 'store_004', address: '321 First St', city: 'city_002', latitude: 37.3382, longitude: -121.8863}, {id: 'store_005', address: '654 Park Ave', city: 'city_002', latitude: 37.3352, longitude: -121.8811}, {id: 'store_006', address: '987 Santa Clara St', city: 'city_002', latitude: 37.3541, longitude: -121.9552}, {id: 'store_007', address: '147 Broadway', city: 'city_003', latitude: 37.8044, longitude: -122.2708}, {id: 'store_008', address: '258 Telegraph Ave', city: 'city_003', latitude: 37.8199, longitude: -122.269}, {id: 'store_009', address: '369 Grand Ave', city: 'city_003', latitude: 37.8103, longitude: -122.2654}, {id: 'store_010', address: '741 Michigan Ave', city: 'city_004', latitude: 41.8781, longitude: -87.6298}, {id: 'store_011', address: '852 State St', city: 'city_004', latitude: 41.8925, longitude: -87.6279}]\n// TODO: Persist the records from `stores` to the Store Type\n\nfor (var i = 0; i < stores.length; i++) {\n  var row = stores[i];\n  Store.make({\n    id: row.id, // Specify the ID here for the record. If empty, a random ID is generated.\n    address: row.address,\n    city: row.city,\n    latitude: row.latitude,\n    longitude: row.longitude\n  }).create()\n}\n\n\n\nproducts = [{'id': 'prod_001', 'name': 'Wireless Bluetooth Headphones', 'description': 'Premium over-ear headphones with noise cancellation and 30-hour battery life', 'category': 'Electronics', 'unitPrice': 129.99}, {'id': 'prod_002', 'name': 'Organic Cotton T-Shirt', 'description': '100% organic cotton crew neck t-shirt available in multiple colors', 'category': 'Clothing', 'unitPrice': 24.99}, {'id': 'prod_003', 'name': 'Stainless Steel Water Bottle', 'description': 'Insulated 32oz water bottle that keeps drinks cold for 24 hours', 'category': 'Home & Kitchen', 'unitPrice': 34.99}, {'id': 'prod_004', 'name': 'Smartphone Case', 'description': 'Protective silicone case compatible with latest smartphone models', 'category': 'Electronics', 'unitPrice': 19.99}, {'id': 'prod_005', 'name': 'Running Shoes', 'description': 'Lightweight athletic shoes with breathable mesh and cushioned sole', 'category': 'Footwear', 'unitPrice': 89.99}, {'id': 'prod_006', 'name': 'Coffee Maker', 'description': '12-cup programmable drip coffee maker with auto shut-off feature', 'category': 'Home & Kitchen', 'unitPrice': 79.99}, {'id': 'prod_007', 'name': 'Denim Jeans', 'description': 'Classic straight-leg jeans made from premium denim fabric', 'category': 'Clothing', 'unitPrice': 59.99}, {'id': 'prod_008', 'name': 'Wireless Charging Pad', 'description': 'Fast wireless charging pad compatible with Qi-enabled devices', 'category': 'Electronics', 'unitPrice': 39.99}, {'id': 'prod_009', 'name': 'Yoga Mat', 'description': 'Non-slip 6mm thick yoga mat with carrying strap', 'category': 'Sports & Outdoors', 'unitPrice': 29.99}, {'id': 'prod_010', 'name': 'Ceramic Dinner Plates Set', 'description': 'Set of 4 microwave and dishwasher safe ceramic plates', 'category': 'Home & Kitchen', 'unitPrice': 49.99}, {'id': 'prod_011', 'name': 'Laptop Backpack', 'description': 'Padded laptop compartment backpack with multiple organizational pockets', 'category': 'Bags & Luggage', 'unitPrice': 69.99}]\n// TODO: Persist the records from `products` to the Product Type\n\nfor (var i = 0; i < products.length; i++) {\n  var row = products[i];\n  Product.make({\n    id: row.id, // Specify the ID here for the record. If empty, a random ID is generated.\n    name: row.name,\n    description: row.description,\n    category: row.category, \n    unitPrice: row.unitPrice\n  }).create()\n}\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"text/plain","value":["\u001b[31m---------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[0m","Error invoking Java method Product#create: The specified ID 'prod_001' already exists for type Product. Please change to a unique ID."]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779387748717,"endTime":1779387748788},"executionOrder":13,"success":false}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Section 3: Type record retrieval","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"There are a two primary ways to retrieve Type records. If you know the ID of the record, you can retrieve it using the `forId` method. Otherwise, if you want to retrieve records on a Type, use the `fetch` method. \n\nFor example, I can retrieve the `City` record with the ID \"RWC\" that was created earlier in [Section 2](#section-2-create-and-update-type-records).","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"rwc = City.forId(\"RWC\")\n\n// Access fields on the City object\nrwc.population","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"text/plain","value":["84292"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779387775281,"endTime":1779387775511},"executionOrder":14,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"To retrieve all `City` records, use the `fetch` method. A similar method, `fetchCount()`, can be used to retrieve the number of persisted records.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// Retrieve all City records as objects\nCity.fetch()","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"c3/notebook","value":["{","\t\"kind\": \"JSON\",","\t\"output\": {","\t\t\"data\": {","\t\t\t\"objs\": [","\t\t\t\t{","\t\t\t\t\t\"id\": \"NYC\",","\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": \"New York City\",","\t\t\t\t\t\"meta\": {","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"appCode\": 1865745090558541600,","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"env\": \"srinat\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"app\": \"academyfundamentals\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"created\": \"2026-05-21T18:12:01Z\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"createdBy\": \"sriram.natarajan@c3.ai\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"updated\": \"2026-05-21T18:12:01Z\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"updatedBy\": \"sriram.natarajan@c3.ai\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-21T18:12:01Z\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"fetchInclude\": \"[]\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"fetchType\": \"City\"","\t\t\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\t\t\"version\": 1,","\t\t\t\t\t\"population\": 8478072,","\t\t\t\t\t\"salesTaxRate\": 8.875","\t\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\t{","\t\t\t\t\t\"id\": \"RWC\",","\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": \"Redwood City\",","\t\t\t\t\t\"meta\": {","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"appCode\": 1865745090558541600,","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"env\": \"srinat\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"app\": \"academyfundamental