uired</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a></h4>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.toJson\\\" title=\\\"method FetchSpec#toJson\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#FetchSpec#toJson\\\">toJson</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.fromJsonString\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fromJsonString</span>(json): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Load the JSON-based representation and reconstruct the corresponding object.</p>\\n<p>fromJsonString is be called on the type be deserialized and must reconstruct an Obj of the appropriate type (which may be\\na type that mixes in the type on which it is called). This means that the resulting object's type will be isA the\\ncalled-on type, but perhaps not identical. In particular, <code>Obj.fromJsonString</code> works for any actual type and will return\\nan instance of the correct type.</p>\\n</div>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">json</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a></h4>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.toJsonString\\\" title=\\\"method FetchSpec#toJsonString\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#FetchSpec#toJsonString\\\">toJsonString</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.fromXmlString\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fromXmlString</span>(xml): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Load the XML-based representation and reconstruct the corresponding object.</p>\\n<p>fromXmlString is be called on the type be deserialized and must reconstruct an Obj of the appropriate type (which\\nmay be a type that mixes in the type on which it is called). This means that the resulting object's type will be\\nisA the called type, but perhaps not identical. In particular, <code>Obj.fromXmlString</code> works for any actual type and\\nwill return an instance of the correct type.</p>\\n</div>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">xml</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a></h4>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.toXmlString\\\" title=\\\"method FetchSpec#toXmlString\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#FetchSpec#toXmlString\\\">toXmlString</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.toBuilder\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">toBuilder</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:ObjBuilder<mixing_FetchSpec>\\\" title=\\\"type ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;\\\">ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:ObjBuilder<mixing_FetchSpec>\\\" title=\\\"type ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;\\\">ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">new ObjBuilder with initial state set to fields of this instance.</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.builder\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">builder</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:ObjBuilder<mixing_FetchSpec>\\\" title=\\\"type ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;\\\">ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:ObjBuilder<mixing_FetchSpec>\\\" title=\\\"type ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;\\\">ObjBuilder&lt;mixing FetchSpec&gt;</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">new ObjBuilder of this instance.</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.fromFields\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fromFields</span>(fields, spec): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Construct instance of this type from provided field values and options</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">fields</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Map<FieldType,_native>\\\" title=\\\"map collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Map&lt;FieldType, native&gt;\\\">map</a>&lt;FieldType, native&gt; <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">spec</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj.MakeSpec\\\" title=\\\"type Obj.MakeSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj.MakeSpec\\\">Obj.MakeSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.fromFields-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fromFields</span>(fields, withDefaults): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Construct an instance of this type from provided fields</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">fields</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Map<FieldType,_any_|_native>\\\" title=\\\"map collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Map&lt;FieldType, any | native&gt;\\\">map</a>&lt;FieldType, <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a><a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyOfType\\\" title=\\\"any of multiple types\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyOfType\\\"> | </a>native&gt; <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Fields to construct the instance of the obj with</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">withDefaults</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">If set, then the Obj is made with default &amp; initial values (required primitive fields e.g. !int32 -&gt; 0) populated</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.withDefaults\\\" title=\\\"method FetchSpec#withDefaults\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#FetchSpec#withDefaults\\\">withDefaults</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.remake\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">remake</span>(other, failIfExtraOrInvalidFields): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Construct an instance of this type from provided instance of a subtype or a \\\"duck type\\\".</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">other</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">failIfExtraOrInvalidFields</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.remakeAs\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">remakeAs</span>(type): <em>O</em>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Creates an obj of the new type with all fields that exist on the original obj that are defined in the new type\\nconverted and copied to the new obj instance. Note, that checking assignability and conversion of field values\\ncould be costly if types have different value types for same fields.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">type</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Type\\\" title=\\\"type Type\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Type\\\">Type</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Type of new obj to return</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <em>O</em>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">new obj of the requested type with all fields present in the original obj that are defined in the new type\\nconverted and copied to it</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.cachedEmptyInst\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">cachedEmptyInst</span>(): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Creates an empty inst using <code>MyType.make()</code> and caches it. Avoid recreating multiple copies of the spec for\\nevery action dispatch. The cached inst can also be used for comparing whether the object is an empty or not\\nWill only create empty instance for immutable Obj e.g. if an Obj is Mutable, this method will throw an error</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:ValueType.defaultEmptyValue\\\" title=\\\"method ValueType#defaultEmptyValue\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#ValueType#defaultEmptyValue\\\">ValueType#defaultEmptyValue</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.toData\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited deprecated\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">toData</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Data\\\" title=\\\"type Data\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Data\\\">Data</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Represent the current obj instance as <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Data\\\" title=\\\"type Data\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Data\\\">Data</a></p>\\n<p class=\\\"deprecated-info\\\">Deprecated: This method will be removed in future releases. (final version 8.8)</p><p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Data\\\" title=\\\"type Data\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Data\\\">Data</a></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.generateObjs\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">generateObjs</span>(spec): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Stream<!mixing_FetchSpec>\\\" title=\\\"stream collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Stream&lt;!mixing FetchSpec&gt;\\\">stream</a>&lt;mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a>&gt; <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Generate a stream of instances of this type. The stream is endless and will call <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.generateObj\\\" title=\\\"method FetchSpec#generateObj\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#FetchSpec#generateObj\\\">#generateObj</a> each time a new\\nvalue is read.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">spec</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj.GenerateSpec\\\" title=\\\"type Obj.GenerateSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj.GenerateSpec\\\">Obj.GenerateSpec</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Stream<!mixing_FetchSpec>\\\" title=\\\"stream collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Stream&lt;!mixing FetchSpec&gt;\\\">stream</a>&lt;mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a>&gt;</h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.generateObj\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">generateObj</span>(spec): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Generate a single instance of this type. The base implementation uses <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DataGenObj\\\" title=\\\"type DataGenObj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DataGenObj\\\">DataGenObj</a> to generate uniform\\nrandom (gibberish) values for all fields, but it may be overridden by specific types with custom logic that\\npopulates fields in a more realistic way.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">spec</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj.GenerateSpec\\\" title=\\\"type Obj.GenerateSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj.GenerateSpec\\\">Obj.GenerateSpec</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.fingerprint\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fingerprint</span>(allIdentifiedRefFields, trackRecursiveRefs, traversedRefs): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:IntType\\\" title=\\\"primitive int\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#IntType\\\">int</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Produce a checksum that can easily be compared to determine if two objects are definitely different. Note that\\nthere is a slight possibility that two objects with the same fingerprint will actually differ.</p>\\n<p>The fingerprint recurses into field values, including collections and referenced Objs. The handling of nested\\n<a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Identified\\\" title=\\\"type Identified\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Identified\\\">identified</a> references (typically entities) differ in that <em>only</em> the <code>id</code> field is included\\nunless the allIdentifiedRefFields option is specified.</p>\\n<p>If the object graph may contain recursive embedded object references, the trackRecursiveRefs option may be used.\\nHowever, maintaining the list of visited objects is costly so this should not be done unnecessarily.</p>\\n</div>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">allIdentifiedRefFields</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">if <code>true</code>, fingerprint individual fields of persistable references, not just the <code>id</code></p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">trackRecursiveRefs</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">if <code>true</code>, a set of referenced objects is maintained to avoid infinite recursion</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">traversedRefs</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:SetBuilder<Obj>\\\" title=\\\"type SetBuilder&lt;Obj&gt;\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#SetBuilder&lt;Obj&gt;\\\">SetBuilder&lt;Obj&gt;</a>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">only considered together with trackRecursiveRefs and if provided then all traversed references are\\nchecked against and added to it</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:IntType\\\" title=\\\"primitive int\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#IntType\\\">int</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">integer fingerprint</p>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"url external\\\" title=\\\"url https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fingerprint_(computing)\\\" href=\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fingerprint_(computing)\\\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fingerprint_(computing)</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.retainedMemory\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">retainedMemory</span>(deep, allMeasured): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:IntType\\\" title=\\\"primitive int\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#IntType\\\">int</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Measures retained memory by this instance.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">deep</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">if true and this instance contains references to other objects also measures memory retained by those</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">allMeasured</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:SetBuilder\\\" title=\\\"type SetBuilder\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#SetBuilder\\\">SetBuilder</a>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">if set then will skip instances that are in the set and will add instances that where measured by this call</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:IntType\\\" title=\\\"primitive int\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#IntType\\\">int</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">retained memory in bytes for this instances</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<h2 class=\\\"section method-section inherited\\\">Methods from Serializable</h2>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.serialize\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">serialize</span>(contentType, toUntyped): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Convert the internal object representation to a string serialized representation of the object.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Serializable\\\" title=\\\"type Serializable\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Serializable\\\">Serializable</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">contentType</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span><span class=\\\"serialized\\\">serialized</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"serialized\\\">Serialized <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:ContentType\\\" title=\\\"type ContentType\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#ContentType\\\">ContentType</a></p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">toUntyped</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">string serialized object representation</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.deserialize\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">deserialize</span>(contentStr, contentType): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Load from contentType representation and reconstruct the corresponding object.</p>\\n<p>fromString is be called on the type be deserialized and must reconstruct an object of the appropriate type\\n(which may be a type that mixes in the type on which it is called). This means that the resulting object's type\\nwill be isA the called-on type, but perhaps not identical. In particular, <code>fromString</code> works for any actual\\ntype and will return an instance of the correct type.</p>\\n</div>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Serializable\\\" title=\\\"type Serializable\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Serializable\\\">Serializable</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">contentStr</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">contentType</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span><span class=\\\"serialized\\\">serialized</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"serialized\\\">Serialized <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:ContentType\\\" title=\\\"type ContentType\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#ContentType\\\">ContentType</a></p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<h2 class=\\\"section method-section inherited\\\">Methods from WithType</h2>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.super\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">super</span>(mixin): !native <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Produce a calling proxy that represents the content of all Obj type's mixins, but not the type itself. This is\\nuseful for redispatching <strong>member</strong> methods reimplemented on this type to a parent implementation:</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"code lang-JavaScript\\\"><code>function toString() {\\n  return this.super().toString() + ', x=' + this.x;\\n}\\n</code></pre>\\n<pre class=\\\"code lang-Python\\\"><code>def toString(this):\\n   return this.super().toString() + ', x=' + this.x\\n</code></pre>\\n<p>To redispatch <strong>static</strong> methods, see <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Type.super\\\" title=\\\"method Type#super\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Type#super\\\">Type#super</a>.</p>\\n<p>Note that this not the same as the language-specific <code>super</code> keyword because it works through the type system and\\nsupports multiple mixins. It behaves like the Python <code>super()</code> function, except called on the instance rather than\\nglobally.</p>\\n<p>If <code>mixin</code> is the implementing type in a client implementation, this will delegate the call to the server.\\nThis can be used to create a local implementation \\\"around\\\" the server implementation for additional caching or\\nother local state management.</p>\\n</div>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:WithType\\\" title=\\\"type WithType\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#WithType\\\">WithType</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">mixin</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Type\\\" title=\\\"type Type\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Type\\\">Type</a>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">if specified, this mixin is used instead or an error is thrown</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns !native <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">\\\"super\\\" calling proxy for this object</p>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Type.super\\\" title=\\\"type Type.super\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Type.super\\\">Type.super</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<h2 class=\\\"section method-section inherited\\\">Methods from FetchFilterSpec</h2>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchSpec.hasTimeRange\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">hasTimeRange</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Determines if the given spec has <a class=\\\"field documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"field:FetchSpec.timeRange\\\" title=\\\"field FetchSpec#timeRange\\\" href=\\\"#FIELD#FetchSpec#timeRange\\\">#timeRange</a> or <a class=\\\"field documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"field:FetchSpec.asOf\\\" title=\\\"field FetchSpec#asOf\\\" href=\\\"#FIELD#FetchSpec#asOf\\\">#asOf</a> field set</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchFilterSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchFilterSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchFilterSpec\\\">FetchFilterSpec</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n</div>\\n\"","\t},","\t\"settings\": {","\t\t\"privateFields\": false,","\t\t\"maxHeight\": 540,","\t\t\"gridRows\": 100,","\t\t\"theme\": \"Default Dark Modern\"","\t}","}"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779387814904,"endTime":1779387816297},"executionOrder":17,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"There are a few fields you may encounter frequently and even use yourself in a `FetchSpec`. \n\n\n| Field                  | Usage       |\n|:-----------------------|:----------------|\n|`limit`                 | The number of objects to return. Fetch returns 2000 objects by default, so if you want to return more, you can raise this limit, or set the limit to `-1` to return all records. |\n|`include`               | The fields to return for each object. This is similar to the `SELECT` clause of a SQL query.. |\n|`filter`                | The records to return based on your filter. This is similar to `WHERE` in SQL. The best practice is to use the `Filter` Type to construct your filters for `fetch` calls. |\n\nThe following cell contains an example of a `FetchSpec` and the configuration options covered in the table.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// Example: Configure a fetch spec for stores.\nspec = FetchSpec.make({\n    filter: Filter.eq('city', 'city_001'), // Use the Filter Type to filter stores that are in city_001.\n    include: 'id, address', // Specify the fields to include in the results. \n    limit: 1 // Limit the results to 1 store.\n})\n\n// Fetch a store using the spec\nStore.fetch(spec)\n\n// You can also create the spec directly in the fetch method.\n/* \nStore.fetch({\n    filter: Filter.eq('city', 'city_001'),\n    include: 'this', // 'this' includes all fields\n    limit: 1\n})\n*/","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"c3/notebook","value":["{","\t\"kind\": \"JSON\",","\t\"output\": {","\t\t\"data\": {","\t\t\t\"objs\": [","\t\t\t\t{","\t\t\t\t\t\"id\": \"store_001\",","\t\t\t\t\t\"meta\": {","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"fetchInclude\": \"[id,address,version]\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"fetchType\": \"Store\"","\t\t\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\t\t\"version\": 1,","\t\t\t\t\t\"address\": \"123 Market St\"","\t\t\t\t}","\t\t\t],","\t\t\t\"count\": 1,","\t\t\t\"hasMore\": true,","\t\t\t\"spec\": {","\t\t\t\t\"offset\": 0,","\t\t\t\t\"limit\": 1,","\t\t\t\t\"filter\": \"city == \\\"city_001\\\"\",","\t\t\t\t\"include\": \"id, address\"","\t\t\t}","\t\t},","\t\t\"isGriddable\": true,","\t\t\"isChartable\": false,","\t\t\"chartMeta\": null,","\t\t\"gridMeta\": {","\t\t\t\"columns\": [","\t\t\t\t{","\t\t\t\t\t\"index\": 0,","\t\t\t\t\t\"label\": \"id\",","\t\t\t\t\t\"valueType\": {","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"modifier\": \"NON_EMPTY\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": \"string\"","\t\t\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": \"id\"","\t\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\t{","\t\t\t\t\t\"index\": 1,","\t\t\t\t\t\"label\": \"address\",","\t\t\t\t\t\"valueType\": {","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": \"string\"","\t\t\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": \"address\"","\t\t\t\t}","\t\t\t],","\t\t\t\"rows\": [","\t\t\t\t{","\t\t\t\t\t\"index\": 0,","\t\t\t\t\t\"label\": \"0\",","\t\t\t\t\t\"labelSource\": 0,","\t\t\t\t\t\"source\": {","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"type\": \"Store\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"id\": \"store_001\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"meta\": {","\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"fetchInclude\": \"[id,address,version]\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"fetchType\": \"Store\"","\t\t\t\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"version\": 1,","\t\t\t\t\t\t\"address\": \"123 Market St\"","\t\t\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\t\t\"cells\": [","\t\t\t\t\t\t{","\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"string\": \"store_001\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"source\": \"store_001\"","\t\t\t\t\t\t},","\t\t\t\t\t\t{","\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"string\": \"123 Market St\",","\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"source\": \"123 Market St\"","\t\t\t\t\t\t}","\t\t\t\t\t]","\t\t\t\t}","\t\t\t],","\t\t\t\"isDataGridValues\": false","\t\t}","\t},","\t\"settings\": {","\t\t\"privateFields\": false,","\t\t\"maxHeight\": 540,","\t\t\"gridRows\": 100,","\t\t\"theme\": \"Default Dark Modern\"","\t}","}"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779387966055,"endTime":1779387966954},"executionOrder":18,"success":true}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// Optional — uncomment the following line to display the Filter Type documentation.\nFilter","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"c3/notebook","value":["{","\t\"kind\": \"TYPEDOC\",","\t\"output\": {","\t\t\"appName\": \"academyfundamentals\",","\t\t\"endpoint\": \"http://stgawstrn1-srinat-c3-k8ssvc-appleader-001:8888/srinat/academyfundamentals\",","\t\t\"typeName\": \"Filter\",","\t\t\"kind\": \"TYPE\",","\t\t\"privateFields\": false,","\t\t\"maxHeight\": 540,","\t\t\"gridRows\": 100,","\t\t\"theme\": \"Default Dark Modern\",","\t\t\"html\": \"<div id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" class=\\\"structure type root\\\">\\n<h1 class=\\\"type root\\\">Type <span class=\\\"name\\\">Filter</span></h1>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Helper C3 Type for building filter expressions.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"mixes\\\"><p>Mixes:</p>\\n<ul class=\\\"mixes\\\">\\n<li class=\\\"mixes\\\"><a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringSerializable\\\" title=\\\"type StringSerializable\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringSerializable\\\">StringSerializable</a></li>\\n<li class=\\\"mixes\\\"><a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DefaultInstance\\\" title=\\\"type DefaultInstance\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DefaultInstance\\\">DefaultInstance</a></li>\\n<li class=\\\"mixes\\\"><a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Spec\\\" title=\\\"type Spec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Spec\\\">Spec</a></li>\\n</ul></div>\\n<h2 class=\\\"section method-section\\\">Methods</h2>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.lit\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">lit</span>(literal): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a string literal to the expression. This can be used for syntax that isn't supported by the builder directly\\nor for other special formatting purposes.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">literal</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">string literal to be added</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.lit-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">lit</span>(literal): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a literal string, as returned by the specified lambda, to the expression. This can be used for syntax that\\nisn't supported by the builder directly or for other special formatting purposes.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">literal</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:LambdaType\\\" title=\\\"lambda\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#LambdaType\\\">lambda</a>(): !<a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">lambda that returns the string literal to be added</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.eq\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">eq</span>(name, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Adds an equality element to the expression. This consists of a simple comparison of a field with a single value,\\nas in the SQL expression \\\"name = <em>value</em>\\\".  The actual expression language syntax is \\\"name == <em>value</em>\\\" where\\n<em>value</em> is formatted and escaped appropriately.</p>\\n<p>Note that if the value argument is a lambda, it will be called to produce the value used.</p>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to compare against</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">value to compare</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.ne\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">ne</span>(name, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a negative equality element to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to compare against</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">value to compare</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.lt\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">lt</span>(name, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a less-than inequality element to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to compare against</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">value to compare</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.le\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">le</span>(name, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a less-than-or-equal-to inequality element to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to compare against</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">value to compare</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.gt\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">gt</span>(name, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a greater-than inequality element to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to compare against</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">value to compare</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.ge\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">ge</span>(name, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a greater-than-or-equal-to inequality element to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to compare against</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">value to compare</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.exists\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">exists</span>(name): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a field existence check to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to check existence of</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.intersects\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">intersects</span>(name, values&hellip;): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"varargs\\\">varargs</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Adds a multi-comparison to the expression.\\n\\\"intersects\\\" is used as a shorthand for an <em>or</em> of many values, particularly when\\nthe number of values is not known in advance.</p>\\n<p>If <em>no</em> values are provided (no arguments are passed), this is equivalent to false.\\nNull and undefined values arguments are ignored.</p>\\n<p>If a single array argument is passed, the values are its elements.</p>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to check existence of</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">values</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Array<any>\\\" title=\\\"array collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Array&lt;any&gt;\\\">[</a> <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> ] <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"varargs\\\">varargs</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">array of values to intersect</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.intersects-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">intersects</span>(name, values): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Adds a multi-comparison to the expression, using the value returned by a lambda.\\n\\\"intersects\\\" is used as a shorthand for an <em>or</em> of many values, particularly when\\nthe number of values is not known in advance.</p>\\n<p>If <em>no</em> values are provided (the lambda returns an empty array), this is equivalent to false.\\nNull and undefined values in the returned array are ignored.</p>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to check existence of</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">values</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:LambdaType\\\" title=\\\"lambda\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#LambdaType\\\">lambda</a>(): !?<a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Array<any>\\\" title=\\\"array collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Array&lt;any&gt;\\\">[</a> <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> ] <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">lambda that returns an array of values; null elements are skipped</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.startsWith\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">startsWith</span>(name, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a prefix match to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to check the prefix of</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">prefix to compare against</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.endsWith\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">endsWith</span>(name, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a suffix match to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to check the suffix of</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">suffix to compare against</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.contains\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">contains</span>(name, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a infix match to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to check the infix of</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">infix to compare against</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.containsIgnoreCase\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">containsIgnoreCase</span>(name, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds a infix match ignoring case to the expression</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">name</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">field to check the infix of</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">infix to compare against</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.not\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">not</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds <code>!</code> to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.and\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">and</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds <code>&amp;&amp;</code> to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.and-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">and</span>(expr): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Returns the conjunction (<code>&amp;&amp;</code> operator) between the instance and the <code>expr</code> filter.\\nIf one of the clause is void, the other is simply returned as is.\\nOtherwise, both clauses are surrounded by parentheses and joined with a <code>&amp;&amp;</code> operator.</p>\\n<p>Example:</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"code lang-JavaScript\\\"><code>const f = Filter.eq(\\\"name\\\", \\\"some value\\\");\\nf.and(Filter.intersects(\\\"category\\\", [\\\"A\\\", \\\"B\\\"])).toString();\\n// '(name == \\\"some value\\\") &amp;&amp; (intersects(category, [\\\"A\\\", \\\"B\\\"]))'\\nf.and('intersects(category, [\\\"A\\\", \\\"B\\\"])').toString();\\n// '(name == \\\"some value\\\") &amp;&amp; (intersects(category, [\\\"A\\\", \\\"B\\\"]))'\\nf.and(\\\"\\\");\\n// 'name == \\\"some value\\\"'\\n</code></pre>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">expr</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"serialized\\\">serialized</span><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Another filter to combine with the current one with a <code>&amp;&amp;</code> operator.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"serialized\\\">Serialized <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Expr\\\" title=\\\"type Expr\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Expr\\\">Expr</a></p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.or\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">or</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds <code>||</code> to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.or-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">or</span>(expr): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Returns the disjunction (<code>||</code> operator) between the instance and the <code>expr</code> filter.\\nIf one of the clause is void, the other is simply returned as is.\\nOtherwise, both clauses are surrounded by parentheses and joined with a <code>||</code> operator.</p>\\n<p>Example:</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"code lang-JavaScript\\\"><code>const f = Filter.eq(\\\"name\\\", \\\"some value\\\");\\nf.or(Filter.intersects(\\\"category\\\", [\\\"A\\\", \\\"B\\\"])).toString();\\n// '(name == \\\"some value\\\") || (intersects(category, [\\\"A\\\", \\\"B\\\"]))'\\nf.or('intersects(category, [\\\"A\\\", \\\"B\\\"])').toString();\\n// '(name == \\\"some value\\\") || (intersects(category, [\\\"A\\\", \\\"B\\\"]))'\\nf.or(\\\"\\\");\\n// 'name == \\\"some value\\\"'\\n</code></pre>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">expr</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"serialized\\\">serialized</span><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Another filter to combine with the current one with a <code>||</code> operator.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"serialized\\\">Serialized <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Expr\\\" title=\\\"type Expr\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Expr\\\">Expr</a></p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.lp\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">lp</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds <code>(</code> to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.rp\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">rp</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Adds <code>)</code> to the expression.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.paren\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">paren</span>(lit): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Equivalent to <code>.lp().lit(value).rp()</code>. May be used to like\\n<code>Filter.eq('id', id).or().paren(Filter.startsWith('name', prefix).and().endsWith('name', suffix))</code></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">lit</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">The filter literal to append in parens. Note this should not be an unquoted value.</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">updated filter</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.toSql\\\" class=\\\"structure method beta\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">toSql</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Converts the current filter into a valid Sql Where Expression</p>\\n<p class=\\\"beta-info\\\">Beta</p><div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.toString\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">toString</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Returns the current <code>value</code> field of the <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a>.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">the value.</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.fromString\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fromString</span>(s): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Generates a <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> from a string.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">s</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">The string to set as the value of the filter.</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">the constructed <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a>.</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.fieldMatchesText\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fieldMatchesText</span>(field, value): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">field</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">value</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">expression for text search (e.g. <code>matchesText(field, value)</code>)</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.inst\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">inst</span>(): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">the default instance to be used when member functions are called on this type. E.g.\\nFileSystem.inst() should return a default file system. It is up to implementation to decide if default\\ninstance is a singleton or not.</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.toJson\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">toJson</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:JsonType\\\" title=\\\"primitive json\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#JsonType\\\">json</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Convert the internal object representation to a JSON object.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:JsonType\\\" title=\\\"primitive json\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#JsonType\\\">json</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">JSON object representation</p>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.fromJson\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#fromJson\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#fromJson\\\">fromJson</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.toJson-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">toJson</span>(include, exclude): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:JsonType\\\" title=\\\"primitive json\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#JsonType\\\">json</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Convert the internal object representation to a JSON object.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">include</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"serialized\\\">serialized</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"serialized\\\">Serialized <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Include\\\" title=\\\"type Include\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Include\\\">Include</a></p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">exclude</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"serialized\\\">serialized</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"serialized\\\">Serialized <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Exclude\\\" title=\\\"type Exclude\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Exclude\\\">Exclude</a></p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:JsonType\\\" title=\\\"primitive json\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#JsonType\\\">json</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">JSON object representation</p>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.fromJson\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#fromJson\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#fromJson\\\">fromJson</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.toJson-3\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">toJson</span>(include, exclude): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:JsonType\\\" title=\\\"primitive json\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#JsonType\\\">json</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Convert the internal object representation to a JSON object.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">include</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Include\\\" title=\\\"type Include\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Include\\\">Include</a>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">exclude</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Exclude\\\" title=\\\"type Exclude\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Exclude\\\">Exclude</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:JsonType\\\" title=\\\"primitive json\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#JsonType\\\">json</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">JSON object representation</p>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.fromJson\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#fromJson\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#fromJson\\\">fromJson</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<h2 class=\\\"section method-section inherited\\\">Methods from StringSerializable</h2>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.make\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">make</span>(s): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Construct an instance of this type from the string. This is an alias for <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.fromString\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#fromString\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#fromString\\\">#fromString</a>, as a specific overload\\nwhen the argument is a known string.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringSerializable\\\" title=\\\"type StringSerializable\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringSerializable\\\">StringSerializable</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">s</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a></h4>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.fromString\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#fromString\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#fromString\\\">fromString</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<h2 class=\\\"section method-section inherited\\\">Methods from Obj</h2>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.make-3\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">make</span>(withDefaults): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Construct an instance of this type with no non-default field values unless explicitly specified by passing param true</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">withDefaults</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">If set, then the Obj is made with default &amp; initial values (required primitive fields e.g. !int32 -&gt; 0)\\npopulated</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.withDefaults\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#withDefaults\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#withDefaults\\\">withDefaults</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.make-4\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">make</span>(fields, withDefaults): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Construct an instance from provided fields</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">fields</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Map<string,_any_|_native>\\\" title=\\\"map collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Map&lt;string, any | native&gt;\\\">map</a>&lt;string, <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a><a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyOfType\\\" title=\\\"any of multiple types\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyOfType\\\"> | </a>native&gt; <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Fields (in the format &lt;field_name, value&gt;) to construct an instance of the obj. Note that \\\"type\\\" as a\\nfield_name will be considered as the actual Obj's type, e.g. Obj.make({\\\"type\\\": \\\"Panda\\\"}) is equivalent\\nto Panda.make()</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">withDefaults</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">If set, then the Obj is made with default &amp; initial values (required primitive fields e.g. !int32\\n-&gt; 0) populated. Passing an empty value for a field will result in the initial value being set if\\nthe field does not <a class=\\\"field documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"field:ValueModifier.PRESERVES_EMPTY\\\" title=\\\"field ValueModifier#PRESERVES_EMPTY\\\" href=\\\"#FIELD#ValueModifier#PRESERVES_EMPTY\\\">preserve empty</a></p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div><div class=\\\"see\\\"><p>See:</p>\\n<ul class=\\\"see\\\">\\n<li class=\\\"see\\\"><a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.fromFields\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#fromFields\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#fromFields\\\">fromFields</a></li>\\n<li class=\\\"see\\\"><a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.beforeMake\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#beforeMake\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#beforeMake\\\">beforeMake</a></li>\\n<li class=\\\"see\\\"><a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.afterMake\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#afterMake\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#afterMake\\\">afterMake</a></li>\\n<li class=\\\"see\\\"><a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.withDefaults\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#withDefaults\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#withDefaults\\\">withDefaults</a></li>\\n</ul></div>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.make-5\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">make</span>(fields, withDefaults): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Construct an instance of this type from provided fields. Note it is more efficient to use <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.fromFields\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#fromFields\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#fromFields\\\">#fromFields</a> and other overloads</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"code lang-JavaScript\\\"><code>User.make({\\n  email: 'joe@smith.com',\\n  realName: 'Joe Smith'\\n})\\n\\nObj.make({\\n  type: 'User',\\n  email: 'joe@smith.com',\\n  realName: 'Joe Smith'\\n})\\n</code></pre>\\n<pre class=\\\"code lang-Python\\\"><code>c3.User.make({\\n  \\\"email\\\": 'joe@smith.com',\\n  \\\"realName\\\": 'Joe Smith'\\n})\\n\\nc3.Obj.make({\\n  \\\"type\\\": 'User',\\n  \\\"email\\\": 'joe@smith.com',\\n  \\\"realName\\\": 'Joe Smith'\\n})\\n\\nc3.User(email='joe@smith.com', realName='Joe Smith')\\n\\nc3.Obj(type='User', email='joe@smith.com', realName='Joe Smith')\\n</code></pre>\\n<p>Note that this is <strong>not</strong> the same as the <a class=\\\"topic documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"topic:serdeser.c3doc\\\" title=\\\"topic serdeser.c3doc\\\" href=\\\"http://stgawstrn1-srinat-c3-k8ssvc-appleader-001:8888/srinat/academyfundamentals/documentation/topic/serdeser.c3doc\\\">serialization format</a>. This is a convenient way to\\nspecify fields and values in the \\\"JSON like\\\" form supported by each language, but the usual serialization rules,\\nsuch as <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Ann.Ser\\\" title=\\\"type Ann.Ser\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Ann.Ser\\\">Ann.Ser</a> do not apply.</p>\\n</div>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">fields</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Fields to construct the instance of the obj with</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">withDefaults</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">If set, then the Obj is made with default &amp; initial values (required primitive fields e.g. !int32 -&gt; 0) populated</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Filter\\\" title=\\\"type Filter\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Filter\\\">Filter</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div><div class=\\\"see\\\"><p>See:</p>\\n<ul class=\\\"see\\\">\\n<li class=\\\"see\\\"><a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.fromFields\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#fromFields\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#fromFields\\\">fromFields</a></li>\\n<li class=\\\"see\\\"><a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.beforeMake\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#beforeMake\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#beforeMake\\\">beforeMake</a></li>\\n<li class=\\\"see\\\"><a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.afterMake\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#afterMake\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#afterMake\\\">afterMake</a></li>\\n<li class=\\\"see\\\"><a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.withDefaults\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#withDefaults\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#withDefaults\\\">withDefaults</a></li>\\n</ul></div>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.type\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">type</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Type\\\" title=\\\"type Type\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Type\\\">Type</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">C3 Type of this instance.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Type\\\" title=\\\"type Type\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Type\\\">Type</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.instanceOf\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">instanceOf</span>(typeName): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Checks whether this Obj is an instance of the specified type by checking both its type and the mixin chain.\\nThis is the most convenient way to ask \\\"is this type usable in a context requiring the other type?\\\"</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">typeName</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">true if this instance is of this type or any of its mixins</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.instanceOf-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">instanceOf</span>(type): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Checks whether this instance is an instance of the specified type by checking both its type and the mixin chain.\\nThis is the most convenient way to ask \\\"is this type usable in a context requiring the other type?\\\"</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">type</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Type\\\" title=\\\"type Type\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Type\\\">Type</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">true if this instance is of this type or any of its mixins</p>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:ValueType.isA\\\" title=\\\"method ValueType#isA\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#ValueType#isA\\\">ValueType#isA</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.isEmptyObj\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">isEmptyObj</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Whether all the fields of this instance are empty.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.isSame\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">isSame</span>(other): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Whether the specified instance represents exactly the same object as this instance.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">other</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.isFieldSet\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">isFieldSet</span>(field): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Used to determine if a field is set. A field is set if a value was provided for that field to a constructor, or\\nif the field value set the its default value by the constructor. A set field is never missing.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">field</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">the field to check</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">whether the specified field is set</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.isFieldSet-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">isFieldSet</span>(field): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Used to determine if a field is set. A field is set if a value was provided for that field to a constructor, or\\nif the field value set the its default value by the constructor. A set field is never missing.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">field</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FieldType\\\" title=\\\"type FieldType\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FieldType\\\">FieldType</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">the field to check</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">whether the specified field is set</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.isFieldMissing\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">isFieldMissing</span>(field): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Used to determine if a field is missing. The value of a missing field is not known, so a missing field's value\\nshould not be used. For example, when <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Fetchable.fetch\\\" title=\\\"method Fetchable#fetch\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Fetchable#fetch\\\">fetching</a> an entity, a field that is not\\n<a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Include\\\" title=\\\"type Include\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Include\\\">included</a> in the fetch is missing. Accessing a missing field will yield an empty value.\\nA missing field is never set.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">field</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">the field to check</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">whether the specified field is missing</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.isFieldMissing-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">isFieldMissing</span>(field): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"final\\\">final</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Used to determine if a field is missing. The value of a missing field is not known, so a missing field's value\\nshould not be used. For example, when <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Fetchable.fetch\\\" title=\\\"method Fetchable#fetch\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Fetchable#fetch\\\">fetching</a> an entity, a field that is not\\n<a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Include\\\" title=\\\"type Include\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Include\\\">included</a> in the fetch is missing. Accessing a missing field will yield an empty value.\\nA missing field is never set.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">field</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FieldType\\\" title=\\\"type FieldType\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FieldType\\\">FieldType</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">the field to check</p>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">whether the specified field is missing</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.fieldValue\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fieldValue</span>(field, defaultToEmpty): <em>T</em> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Returns value of the given field.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">field</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Field to return the value for\\ndefaultToEmpty\\nwill return default empty value if field is missing</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">defaultToEmpty</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <em>T</em></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.fieldValue-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fieldValue</span>(field, defaultToEmpty): <em>T</em> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Returns value of the given field type. Be sure to use the FieldType instance for the exact same type as the type of\\nthe obj.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">field</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FieldType\\\" title=\\\"type FieldType\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FieldType\\\">FieldType</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span></span>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Field to return the value for\\ndefaultToEmpty\\nwill return default empty value if field is missing</p>\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">defaultToEmpty</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <em>T</em></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">value for the given field</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.fieldValues\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fieldValues</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Array<FieldValue>\\\" title=\\\"array collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Array&lt;FieldValue&gt;\\\">[</a> <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FieldValue\\\" title=\\\"type FieldValue\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FieldValue\\\">FieldValue</a> ] <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Returns all non empty field values. Note that it is recommended to use <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.eachFieldValue\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#eachFieldValue\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#eachFieldValue\\\">#eachFieldValue</a> instead</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Array<FieldValue>\\\" title=\\\"array collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Array&lt;FieldValue&gt;\\\">[</a> <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FieldValue\\\" title=\\\"type FieldValue\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FieldValue\\\">FieldValue</a> ]</h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.fieldValuesByOrdinal\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fieldValuesByOrdinal</span>(skipTrailingEmpty): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Array<any>\\\" title=\\\"array collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Array&lt;any&gt;\\\">[</a> <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> ] <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Returns all field values including empty ones as array where value of a field is at corresponding ordinal position.\\nUnless <code>skipTrailingEmpty</code> parameter is set and there are trailing empty values resulting array has same size as\\n#dataFieldTypes</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">skipTrailingEmpty</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Array<any>\\\" title=\\\"array collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Array&lt;any&gt;\\\">[</a> <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a> ]</h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.fieldValuesByFieldType\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fieldValuesByFieldType</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Map<FieldType,_any>\\\" title=\\\"map collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Map&lt;FieldType, any&gt;\\\">map</a>&lt;FieldType, <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a>&gt; <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Returns all non empty field values by field type. Note that it is recommended to use <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.eachFieldValue\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#eachFieldValue\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#eachFieldValue\\\">#eachFieldValue</a> instead</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Map<FieldType,_any>\\\" title=\\\"map collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Map&lt;FieldType, any&gt;\\\">map</a>&lt;FieldType, <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a>&gt;</h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:Filter.fieldValuesByFieldName\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">fieldValuesByFieldName</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Map<string,_any>\\\" title=\\\"map collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Map&lt;string, any&gt;\\\">map</a>&lt;string, <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:AnyType\\\" title=\\\"any\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#AnyType\\\">any</a>&gt; <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Returns all non empty field values by field name. Note that it is recommended to use <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Filter.eachFieldValue\\\" title=\\\"method Filter#eachFieldValue\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Filter#eachFieldValue\\\">#eachFieldValue</a> instead</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Map<string,_any>\\\" title=\\\"map collection\\\" href=\\\