9192231,"endTime":1779389192418},"executionOrder":37,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"There's one more step to using Type records that were retrieved using fetch. The fetch method returns a list of Type objects wrapped around a separate Type, `FetchResult`. The `FetchResult` object contains query metadata, like the options in the FetchSpec and the number of records returned, and the Type records, accessible through the `objs` field.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// Uncomment the following line to display the FetchResult Type documentation.\nFetchResult","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"c3/notebook","value":["{","\t\"kind\": \"TYPEDOC\",","\t\"output\": {","\t\t\"appName\": \"academyfundamentals\",","\t\t\"endpoint\": \"http://stgawstrn1-srinat-c3-k8ssvc-appleader-001:8888/srinat/academyfundamentals\",","\t\t\"typeName\": \"FetchResult\",","\t\t\"kind\": \"TYPE\",","\t\t\"privateFields\": false,","\t\t\"maxHeight\": 540,","\t\t\"gridRows\": 100,","\t\t\"theme\": \"Default Dark Modern\",","\t\t\"html\": \"<div id=\\\"type:FetchResult\\\" class=\\\"structure type root\\\">\\n<h1 class=\\\"type root\\\">Type <span class=\\\"name\\\">FetchResult</span></h1>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Result type returned from a variety of functions that fetch results from any datastore (e.g.\\n<a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Persistable.fetch\\\" title=\\\"method Persistable#fetch\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Persistable#fetch\\\">Persistable#fetch</a> etc.)</p>\\n<p class=\\\"variable\\\">Type Variable <span class=\\\"name\\\">T</span></p>\\n<div class=\\\"mixes\\\"><p>Mixes:</p>\\n<ul class=\\\"mixes\\\">\\n<li class=\\\"mixes\\\"><a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DataGriddable\\\" title=\\\"type DataGriddable\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DataGriddable\\\">DataGriddable</a></li>\\n<li class=\\\"mixes\\\"><a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Refreshable\\\" title=\\\"type Refreshable\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Refreshable\\\">Refreshable</a></li>\\n<li class=\\\"mixes\\\"><a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Result\\\" title=\\\"type Result\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Result\\\">Result</a></li>\\n</ul></div>\\n<p class=\\\"use\\\">Used by <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:App.Alert.FetchResult\\\" title=\\\"type App.Alert.FetchResult\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#App.Alert.FetchResult\\\">App.Alert.FetchResult</a></p>\\n<h2 class=\\\"section field-section\\\">Fields</h2>\\n<div id=\\\"field:FetchResult.objs\\\" class=\\\"structure field\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">objs</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Array<T>\\\" title=\\\"array collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Array&lt;T&gt;\\\">[</a> <em>T</em> ]</h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Returned list of objs that satisfied input the <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a>.</p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"field:FetchResult.count\\\" class=\\\"structure field\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">count</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:IntType\\\" title=\\\"primitive int\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#IntType\\\">int</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Number of returned objs.</p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"field:FetchResult.hasMore\\\" class=\\\"structure field\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">hasMore</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">If the <a class=\\\"field documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"field:FetchSpec.limit\\\" title=\\\"field FetchSpec#limit\\\" href=\\\"#FIELD#FetchSpec#limit\\\">FetchSpec#limit</a> was set to less than the actual number of qualifying objs, this flag will be set to\\ntrue to indicate that there were more objs that were not returned.</p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"field:FetchResult.queryPlans\\\" class=\\\"structure field\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">queryPlans</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Array<QueryPlan>\\\" title=\\\"array collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Array&lt;QueryPlan&gt;\\\">[</a> <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:QueryPlan\\\" title=\\\"type QueryPlan\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#QueryPlan\\\">QueryPlan</a> ]</h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">If the type being fetched from is a <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Persistable\\\" title=\\\"type Persistable\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Persistable\\\">Persistable</a> type and <a class=\\\"field documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"field:FetchSpec.explain\\\" title=\\\"field FetchSpec#explain\\\" href=\\\"#FIELD#FetchSpec#explain\\\">FetchSpec#explain</a> was set to true, returns\\nthe database query plans for all queries issued for the <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:Persistable.fetch\\\" title=\\\"method Persistable#fetch\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#Persistable#fetch\\\">Persistable#fetch</a> request.</p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"field:FetchResult.spec\\\" class=\\\"structure field\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">spec</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Original spec passed to <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Fetchable.fetch\\\" title=\\\"type Fetchable.fetch\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Fetchable.fetch\\\">Fetchable.fetch</a>.</p>\\n</div>\\n<h2 class=\\\"section method-section\\\">Methods</h2>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.first\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">first</span>(): <em>T</em> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <em>T</em></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">first result or null.</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.only\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">only</span>(failIfNotSingleton): <em>T</em> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">failIfNotSingleton</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <em>T</em></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">only result or null if no or more then 1 results.</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.toDataGrid\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">toDataGrid</span>(spec): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DataGrid\\\" title=\\\"type DataGrid\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DataGrid\\\">DataGrid</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Make a tabular representation of the returned objects with their fields as columns.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">spec</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DataGrid.LoadSpec\\\" title=\\\"type DataGrid.LoadSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DataGrid.LoadSpec\\\">DataGrid.LoadSpec</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DataGrid\\\" title=\\\"type DataGrid\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DataGrid\\\">DataGrid</a></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.toData\\\" class=\\\"structure method deprecated\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">toData</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Data\\\" title=\\\"type Data\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Data\\\">Data</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Represent the current obj instance as <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Data\\\" title=\\\"type Data\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Data\\\">Data</a></p>\\n<p class=\\\"deprecated-info\\\">Deprecated: This method will be removed in future releases. (final version 8.8)</p><div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Data\\\" title=\\\"type Data\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Data\\\">Data</a></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.of\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">of</span>(objs): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchResult\\\" title=\\\"type FetchResult\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchResult\\\">FetchResult</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Produce a sample fetch result as though the specified objects had been fetched.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">objs</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Array<T>\\\" title=\\\"array collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Array&lt;T&gt;\\\">[</a> <em>T</em> ]\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchResult\\\" title=\\\"type FetchResult\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchResult\\\">FetchResult</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.of-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">of</span>(objs, spec): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchResult\\\" title=\\\"type FetchResult\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchResult\\\">FetchResult</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Produce a sample fetch result as though the specified objects had been fetched, along with the spec that\\nrepresents how they were produced.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">objs</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Array<T>\\\" title=\\\"array collection\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Array&lt;T&gt;\\\">[</a> <em>T</em> ]\\n</li>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">spec</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchSpec\\\" title=\\\"type FetchSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchSpec\\\">FetchSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchResult\\\" title=\\\"type FetchResult\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchResult\\\">FetchResult</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.isRefreshable\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">isRefreshable</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<div class=\\\"description\\\">\\n<p>Whether this particular instance supports <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:FetchResult.refresh\\\" title=\\\"method FetchResult#refresh\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#FetchResult#refresh\\\">#refresh</a>.</p>\\n<p>By default this is implemented to return <code>true</code>, but if a type that mixes in <strong>Refreshable</strong> sometimes has\\ninstances that <em>cannot</em> be refreshed, it should override this to return the status as appropriate.</p>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<h2 class=\\\"section method-section inherited\\\">Methods from DataGriddable</h2>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.setDefaultSpec\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">setDefaultSpec</span>(spec) <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Since there is no good way to pass in the spec when using the automatic visualization, it's possible to statically\\nset the default values in the local (client) environment. This spec will be used for the #_reprHtml method where\\nno spec may be passed.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DataGriddable\\\" title=\\\"type DataGriddable\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DataGriddable\\\">DataGriddable</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter optional\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">spec</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DataGrid.HtmlSpec\\\" title=\\\"type DataGrid.HtmlSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DataGrid.HtmlSpec\\\">DataGrid.HtmlSpec</a>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.defaultSpec\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">defaultSpec</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DataGrid.HtmlSpec\\\" title=\\\"type DataGrid.HtmlSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DataGrid.HtmlSpec\\\">DataGrid.HtmlSpec</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"static\\\">static</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Get the default spec for the local (client) environment. Note that there may be a default value with values\\nextracted from the current environment. For example in Jupyter, display settings are taken from the current\\n<a class=\\\"url external\\\" title=\\\"url https://pandas.pydata.org/\\\" href=\\\"https://pandas.pydata.org/\\\">pandas</a> settings.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DataGriddable\\\" title=\\\"type DataGriddable\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DataGriddable\\\">DataGriddable</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:DataGrid.HtmlSpec\\\" title=\\\"type DataGrid.HtmlSpec\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#DataGrid.HtmlSpec\\\">DataGrid.HtmlSpec</a></h4>\\n</div><p class=\\\"see\\\">See <a class=\\\"method documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"method:FetchResult.setDefaultSpec\\\" title=\\\"method FetchResult#setDefaultSpec\\\" href=\\\"#METHOD#FetchResult#setDefaultSpec\\\">setDefaultSpec</a></p>\\n</div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.refresh\\\" class=\\\"structure method\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">refresh</span>(): mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchResult\\\" title=\\\"type FetchResult\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchResult\\\">FetchResult</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Produce a new instance with updated state representing the same query as originally performed. This can be called\\nby UIs or other state-management applications to get the latest results.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns mixing <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:FetchResult\\\" title=\\\"type FetchResult\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#FetchResult\\\">FetchResult</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<h2 class=\\\"section method-section inherited\\\">Methods from Obj</h2>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.type\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">type</span>(): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Type\\\" title=\\\"type Type\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Type\\\">Type</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">C3 Type of this instance.</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Type\\\" title=\\\"type Type\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Type\\\">Type</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span></h4>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.instanceOf\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">instanceOf</span>(typeName): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Checks whether this Obj is an instance of the specified type by checking both its type and the mixin chain.\\nThis is the most convenient way to ask \\\"is this type usable in a context requiring the other type?\\\"</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">typeName</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:StringType\\\" title=\\\"primitive string\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#StringType\\\">string</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span>\\n</li>\\n</ol></div>\\n<div class=\\\"returns\\\"><h4>Returns <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a></h4>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">true if this instance is of this type or any of its mixins</p>\\n</div></div>\\n<div id=\\\"method:FetchResult.instanceOf-2\\\" class=\\\"structure method inherited\\\">\\n<h3><span class=\\\"name\\\">instanceOf</span>(type): <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:BooleanType\\\" title=\\\"primitive boolean\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#BooleanType\\\">boolean</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"member\\\">member</span><span class=\\\"overloaded\\\">overloaded</span><span class=\\\"inherited\\\">inherited</span></span></h3>\\n<p class=\\\"description\\\">Checks whether this instance is an instance of the specified type by checking both its type and the mixin chain.\\nThis is the most convenient way to ask \\\"is this type usable in a context requiring the other type?\\\"</p>\\n<p class=\\\"inherited-from\\\">Inherited from <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Obj\\\" title=\\\"type Obj\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Obj\\\">Obj</a></p>\\n<div class=\\\"parameters\\\"><h4>Parameters:</h4>\\n<ol>\\n<li class=\\\"parameter required\\\"><span class=\\\"name\\\">type</span>: <a class=\\\"type documentation\\\" data-to-id=\\\"type:Type\\\" title=\\\"type Type\\\" href=\\\"#TYPE#Type\\\">Type</a> <span class=\\\"attributes\\\"><span class=\\\"required\\\">required</span><span class=\\\"non-empty\\\">non-empty</span></span