": {","\t\t\"privateFields\": false,","\t\t\"maxHeight\": 540,","\t\t\"gridRows\": 100,","\t\t\"theme\": \"Default Dark Modern\"","\t}","}"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779390517753,"endTime":1779390517856},"executionOrder":46,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Section 4: Record removal and lab cleanup","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Removing a single Type record requires knowing the ID of the object. You call `remove()` on the Type record itself.\n\nIn the following cell, `remove` is called on the `City` object with the ID \"RWC.\"","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"City.forId(\"RWC\").remove()","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"text/plain","value":["true"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779390522168,"endTime":1779390522427},"executionOrder":47,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"If you want to remove batches of records, use the `removeAll()` method. This takes in two arguments:\n\n- A spec, to specify an options for the Type records you want to remove. For example, you can specify a filter to remove only certain objects. Use `null` for this argument to remove all persisted records.\n- A confirmation boolean.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"City.removeAll(null, true)","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"text/plain","value":["1"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779390526713,"endTime":1779390526788},"executionOrder":48,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n<h4>Activity 4.1</h4>\n\nRemove all <code>Store</code> and <code>Product</code> records.\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// TODO: Remove all Store and Product records that were created in this lab.\n// Remove all Store records\nStore.removeAll(null, true);\n\n// Remove all Product records\nProduct.removeAll(null, true);","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"text/plain","value":["11"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779390662841,"endTime":1779390662932},"executionOrder":49,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Summary","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Congratulations! 🎉 You learned how to work with persisted Type instances and perform CRUD methods on them. The following table recaps the methods that were covered in this lab.\n\n| Method                 | Use case        |\n|:-----------------------|:----------------|\n|`create()`              | Write an Entity Type object to the database. |\n|`forId()`               | Retrieve a single Type object by ID. |\n|`fetch()`               | Retrieve Type **objects** that match any conditions, if specified. |\n|`fetchCount()`          | Retrieve the number of records saved to a Persistable Type that match a specification. |\n|`upsert()`${^\\dagger}$  | Update an existing record or create a new one if it doesn't exist.|\n|`merge()`               | Create a new record if it doesn't exist or only update the record with the specified fields. |\n|`remove()`              | Delete a Type record from the database. |\n|`removeAll()`           | Delete all Type records, or those that match a condition, from the database. |\n\n${^\\dagger}$ **Reminder**: If you do not specify all existing fields, it will overwrite any missing fields with `null`.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"---","output":[],"executionSummary":{}}],"metadata":{"id":"4ad9bc6b-1fae-4de1-b47f-96ac2e6376d4","appName":"academyfundamentals","serializerVersion":"1","runtime":"js-rhino"}}